ttps://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQIF2FoQzYV7MAknxYC2rrEQwVX1XDs9KlK8lrLv5BbL390LXx14USscdt7FIW5VR3KpP0";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:350;s:6:"height";i:823;s:6:"source";s:78:"https://marvinsgaragedoors.com/2018/03/05/reasons-garage-door-wont-open-close/";s:6:"domain";s:22:"marvinsgaragedoors.com";}i:20;a:11:{s:7:"keyword";s:46:"why does my garage door only open a few inches";s:4:"slug";s:46:"why-does-my-garage-door-only-open-a-few-inches";s:5:"title";s:117:"Want To Park Your Truck In The Garage For Once Home With Property Garage Doors Garage Door Sizes Garage Door Makeover";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:71:"https://i.pinimg.com/736x/4e/68/50/4e6850f40ec0886d78206ef6a2bca860.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcRw19DfV8UNI-nyBC0Alyd6HrZLMJpfEuMeNw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:480;s:6:"height";i:640;s:6:"source";s:49:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/748934613032657378/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:57:{i:0;s:50:"Why Garage Door Only Opens A Few Inches And Stops.";i:1;s:123:"The most common reason why the garage door opens a few inches and then stops is most likely because of the spring assembly.";i:2;s:79:"If garage door springs are not adjusted correctly the doors arent able to open.";i:3;s:40:"Try to operate the garage door manually.";i:4;s:76:"This helps you determine if the problem is related to the door or the motor.";i:5;s:119:"The garage door can be operated manually by disconnecting the garage door opener from the door using the red pull cord.";i:6;s:66:"If the door is working properly it should be easy to lift by hand.";i:7;s:57:"Just a few inches can make a big differenceVisit us here.";i:8;s:193:"If you release the door from the opener using the release cord see image below you should be able to lift the door to half open by hand and the door should stay at that point if you release it.";i:9;s:40:"If not there is a problem with the door.";i:10;s:100:"There could be a bind or drag in the door mechanism or the springs may be damaged or need adjusting.";i:11;s:158:"The most likely cause for a garage door to only open a few inches when hitting the garage door opener remote control or the garage door opener wall button is.";i:12;s:80:"Liftmaster garage door only opens and shuts a few inches after gear replacement.";i:13;s:64:"I just changed out the gears with a replacement kit from Amazon.";i:14;s:57:"After I replaced the hears I hung the garage door opener.";i:15;s:113:"Now Im having and issue where the garage only opens a couple inches and then closes a couple of inches and stops.";i:16;s:105:"My rolling panel garage door only opens about 6 inches and then stops - does not go back down just stops.";i:17;s:116:"I tried to spray the rollers wWD 40 and see that thats not the thing to dobut now Im stuck not being able to get in.";i:18;s:119:"There is nothing in the way of the sensors - altho I do belive that they are primarily for saftey when the door closes.";i:19;s:80:"I have a Craftsman 12 HP garage door opener from 1997 on one of my garage doors.";i:20;s:55:"Recently it will only open the door 6 inches then stop.";i:21;s:71:"I have to hit the button maybe 15 times to get it to go up all the way.";i:22;s:115:"Once I get the door up it will go down half way then stop and I have to do through the same process to get it down.";i:23;s:84:"Disconnect the opener from the door itself like so and open it manually a few times.";i:24;s:206:"Id bet a small fortune that your eyes are getting bounced around while it is openingshutting and disrupting the process but you will want to be sure you dont have anything major going on by doing the above.";i:25;s:54:"Tighten and re-align your eyes and you should be fine.";i:26;s:58:"My garage door will open only a few inches and then stops.";i:27;s:49:"Clicking the remote at that point just closes it.";i:28;s:71:"When my wife clicked to open it I was able to manually help it to open.";i:29;s:27:"Garage door opener problem.";i:30;s:154:"Slipping down a few inches after opening Posted by NashBamaFan on 51016 at 1235 pm to sicboy Probably have 2 springs above door and one of them is broken.";i:31;s:109:"The one that is not is not strong enough to hold door up on its own but strong enough to still open the door.";i:32;s:37:"Well diet diet diet its good for you.";i:33;s:133:"Then when your waist size is anywhere fron 20-30 inches youll be able to do the limbo dance in the 10 opening below your garage door.";i:34;s:32:"And itll be great for your back.";i:35;s:118:"As well that 10 opening will be a novel way to ventilate your garage especially of CO CO2 hydrocarbons benzene dioxin.";i:36;s:85:"If your garage door opens and suddenly stops it might be because of your logic board.";i:37;s:60:"The logic board receives and responds signals to any remote.";i:38;s:110:"You might need to consider replacing it if your door is not working properly or you may purchase a new opener.";i:39;s:142:"The door should open and close easily and it should stay partway open as well as fully closed and fully open while not attached to the opener.";i:40;s:89:"If the door operates fine manually then you know that the opener is creating the problem.";i:41;s:73:"Door wont open by using the remote and I have no other way to get inside.";i:42;s:23:"Betsy on April 16 2017.";i:43;s:54:"Garage door will only open if we hold the button down.";i:44;s:44:"It will only open a few inches from the car.";i:45;s:19:"Stress on the door.";i:46;s:113:"In the fully open or fully closed position the garage doors system is under the least stress from spring tension.";i:47;s:207:"Since leaving it fully open isnt a safe idea unattended homeowners who leave the garage up just a few inches may vent some air but are overall adding to the strain on the door system decreasing its lifespan.";i:48;s:177:"If the motor shaft moves back and forth through the motor more than 116th of an inch during operation it could lead to the door traveling only a short distance before reversing.";i:49;s:94:"Ensure the motor shaft is tightened enough so that there is not too much endplay in the shaft.";i:50;s:78:"A faulty logic board could also be a reason your garage door opens then stops.";i:51;s:81:"This board electrically controls your garage door and will fail if it shorts out.";i:52;s:86:"Depending on how old your garage door opener is you may want to replace it if its old.";i:53;s:26:"Close the door completely.";i:54;s:78:"Pull the emergency release cord to disengage the opener trolley from the door.";i:55;s:31:"Manually lift the door by hand.";i:56;s:148:"If the door opens without a hitch the fault lies with the automatic opener but if you can only open the door halfway the problem is the door itself.";}}